122
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,840
Serve you right, cheeky monkey.

123
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:47,880
Grandma, please help. They are ganging up on me.

124
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,240
I also agree with them.

125
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,360
Awwww

126
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,760
Why is everyone ganging up on me?

127
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:58,200
Wait, is that Phaya?

128
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,800
Why is he here?

129
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,280
I don’t know.

130
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:05,560
Is she the girl who came to see him at our unit?

131
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:08,160
But who’s the other girl?

132
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,840
No idea too.

133
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,400
Maybe she’s also his friend.

134
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:19,520
I don’t think so. As a relationship guru,
I’m sure both of them are not his friends.

135
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:23,640
One is probably his girlfriend. The other must be his fling.

136
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:26,320
Let’s get to work.

137
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:35,920
Please excuse me,
I have to get ready for the exhibition. It’s going to start soon.

138
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:37,840
- See you later then.
- Okay

139
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,720
See you.

140
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:53,160
Tell everyone to get ready in their position.

141
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,160
Yes, Inspector.

142
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:58,000
The VIP guest is going to arrive in 10 minutes.
Yes, sir.

143
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:04,000
Tharn, stay focus. Don’t try to do something silly, okay?

144
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,400
Don’t worry. If I could, I would’ve already done it..

145
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:12,120
I know better than to mix work with personal matters.

146
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:43,640
I never thought the Commisioner would send you to take care of me.

147
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:46,800
How I’m glad to meet you again, Inspector.

148
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:49,800
I’m sure we’ll meet again more often.

149
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:54,200
My condolences to you and your team, Inspector.

150
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:59,840
For losing your favourite assistant.
I’m really sorry that our country has lost another decent man.

151
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,520
He died in the line of duty.

152
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:06,160
I pray for all of them to rest in peace.

153
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:11,360
They all lost their lives to serve the law.

154
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:15,480
I also hope the law would be powerful enough to punish those who have done wrong.

155
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:24,520
Yes. I too hope their sacrifices wouldn’t be a waste.

156
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,360
Please excuse me, Inspector.

157
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,160
Okay.

158
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:37,280
Good evening, Mr. Montree.

159
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:45,040
Have we ever met before? You look very familiar.

160
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,840
Probably my father. He was also a police officer.

161
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,000
You probably met my fathre before.

162
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:55,920
Hmm, a police officer?

163
00:16:57,240 --> 00:17:01,160
He was an inspector. He and my mother died...

164
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:05,560
after being framed in a car accident 10 years ago.

165
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:13,680
Ladies and gentlemen, please come inside. The exhibition is about to start in 5 minutes.

166
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:21,040
Well then, if you need any help, please let me know.

167
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:36,000
Hey, didnt I tell you to calm down?

168
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:43,600
Tharn, can I have a word with you?

169
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:48,880
Yes, sir.

170
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:54,960
What is it, Inspector?

171
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:58,360
Let me remind you again that our job today...

172
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:02,640
is to protect the safety of the VIP guests.

173
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,160
Yes, sir.

174
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:09,120
I just didn’t expect that the VIP guests also include the Minister.

175
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:17,080
Inspector knows, right? The story behind Mr. Montree and the drug trade.
Our job requires us to strictly follow the rules and code of conduct.

176
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:19,040
He attends this event as a guest.

177
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:24,640
Or have you found any evidence which points out that he is the suspect in this event?

178
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,720
No, sir.

179
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,800
Then just do your job.

180
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:29,200
Yes, sir.

181
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:07,080
Phaya, where are you going? The exhibhition is about to start.

182
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:08,400
Where are you going?

183
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:10,160
Are you going to see your colleague?

184
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:14,160
